{"version":1,"entries":{"person_3388218_translations":{"at":1773470199006,"data":{"id":3388218,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Hayato Dojima (堂島 颯人, Dōjima Hayato, June 16, 1995) is a Japanese voice actor from Fukuoka Prefecture. He is affiliated with Across Entertainment.","name":"Hayato Dojima","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"Hayato Dojima (堂島 颯人, Dōjima Hayato, 16 de junio de 1995) es un actor de voz (seiyuu) japonés de la prefectura de Fukuoka. Está afiliado a Across Entertainment.","name":"Hayato Dojima","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"堂島颯人","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"堂岛飒人","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Hajato Dódžima","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Хаято Доджіма","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"堂島颯人是日本的男性聲優。出身於福岡縣，所屬公司為 ACROSS ENTERTAINMENT。","name":"堂島颯人","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"堂島颯人是日本的男性聲優。出身於福岡縣，所屬公司為 ACROSS ENTERTAINMENT。","name":"堂島颯人","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Хаято Додзима","primary":false}}]}},"person_928301_translations":{"at":1773196182935,"data":{"id":928301,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Refet Abazi","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"MK","iso_639_1":"mk","name":"","english_name":"Macedonian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Refet Abazi","primary":true}}]}},"movie_1493591_keywords":{"at":1773211329658,"data":{"id":1493591,"keywords":[]}},"person_18491_translations":{"at":1773319436176,"data":{"id":18491,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"Kitzl wurde im rumänischen Banat geboren, in einem Dorf, das nur wenige Kilometer vom Geburtsort der Literaturnobelpreisträgerin Herta Müller entfernt liegt. Seine Familie gehörte zur deutschsprachigen Minderheit der Banater Schwaben.\n\nEr absolvierte von 1969 bis 1973 ein insg. vierjähriges Studium an der Staatlichen Film- und Schauspielhochschule in Bukarest. Bereits während seines Studiums spielte er am Deutschen Staatstheater Temeswar.  1977 kam Kitzl als Spätaussiedler nach Deutschland.\n\nEr hatte Theaterengagements in Essen, am Stadttheater Bern, am Schauspielhaus Frankfurt, am Schauspielhaus Köln (in der Spielzeit 1984/85 als La Hire in Die Jungfrau von Orleans; Regie: Jürgen Flimm) und am Deutschen Schauspielhaus Hamburg. 1987 war er von Peter Zadek an das Deutsche Schauspielhaus Hamburg engagiert worden, wo er 1987 als Reineke Fuchs von Johann Wolfgang von Goethe in der Regie von Michael Bogdanov auftrat. Weitere Engagements hatte er am Schauspielhaus Düsseldorf (1993 als Basow in Sommergäste von Maxim Gorki) und am Theater in der Josefstadt in Wien.\n\nErste Filmrollen spielte Kitzl Ende der 1970er Jahre in Rumänien. Ab Anfang der 1980er war er regelmäßig in deutschsprachigen Kino- und Fernsehproduktionen zu sehen. Kitzl übernahm dabei meist prägnante Nebenrollen. Oft spielte er Figuren mit Migrationshintergrund. Er wurde, aufgrund seines südländischen Aussehens, häufig als Türke, Italiener, Grieche, Rumäne oder Araber besetzt.","name":"","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Albert Kitzl","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CH","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Albert Kitzl","primary":true}}]}},"person_144655_translations":{"at":1773470200432,"data":{"id":144655,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Tomokazu Sugita is a Japanese voice actor who was born on October 11, 1980 in Saitama, Japan. Previously affiliated with Atomic Monkey, he is now the CEO of AGRS Co., Ltd. His bloodtype is B.\n\nSugita and fellow seiyuu Narita Ken are sometimes referred to as \"brothers\" due to a joke made during Live Pastel Collection 2003. During an Omaera No Tame Darou event, hosts Toshiyuki Morikawa and Nobuyuki Hiyama asked Sugita how they were similar. His answer was that both of them rarely blink, making eye-to-eye contact with either a frightening encounter.\n\nSugita has also had a close friendship with fellow seiyuu Yuichi Nakamura since 2001. Both play male leads in two anime adapted from Key visual novels, Yuichi Aizawa of Kanon and Tomoya Okazaki of Clannad, respectively.\n\nSugita won for \"Best Supporting Actor\" in the Third Seiyu Awards.\n\nOn April 1, 2020, he left Atomic Monkey, where he had belonged for many years, and on October 11, 2019 he established AGRS Co., Ltd., where he serves as the representative director.","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"杉田智和，日本著名声优。在其代表作品中常出演擅长吐槽的男主角（特别是凉宫春日中的阿虚），号称“第一吐槽男”。兴趣是作词、编写脚本。专长是按摩、少林寺拳法初段。\n\n杉田智和在声优界亲近的友人有中村悠一、铃村健一、樱井孝宏、小野大辅、神谷浩史等人。另外与同为声优的铃木达央、羽多野涉、寺岛拓笃、市来光弘等人关系友好，合称为“杉田组”。\n\n杉田智和2009年获得声优奖男优部门配角赏。","name":"杉田智和","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"杉田智和是日本的男性聲優。出身於埼玉縣比企郡嵐山町，所屬公司為自己成立的個人事務所 AGRS。","name":"杉田智和","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"杉田智和","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"스기타 토모카즈","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"DE","iso_639_1":"de","name":"Deutsch","english_name":"German","data":{"biography":"","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"ES","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español","english_name":"Spanish","data":{"biography":"Tomokazu Sugita (杉田 智和, Sugita Tomokazu, nacido el 11 de octubre de 1980 ) es un actor de doblaje (seiyuu) japonés de la prefectura de Saitama, Japón. Anteriormente afiliado a Atomic Monkey, ahora es el director ejecutivo de AGRS Co., Ltd. Su tipo de sangre es B.\n\nA Sugita y su compañero seiyuu Narita Ken a veces se les llama «hermanos» debido a una broma hecha durante Live Pastel Collection 2003. Durante un evento de Omaera no Tame Darou, los presentadores Toshiyuki Morikawa y Nobuyuki Hiyama le preguntaron a Sugita en qué se parecían. Su respuesta fue que ambos rara vez parpadean, haciendo del contacto visual con cualquiera de ellos un encuentro aterrador.\n\nSugita también ha tenido una estrecha amistad con su compañero seiyuu Yuichi Nakamura desde 2001. Ambos interpretan protagonistas masculinos en dos animes adaptados de las novelas visuales de Key, Yuichi Aizawa de Kanon y Tomoya Okazaki de Clannad, respectivamente.\n\nSugita ganó el premio a Mejor actor de reparto en los terceros premios Seiyu.\n\nEl 1 de abril de 2020 dejó Atomic Monkey, donde había pertenecido durante muchos años, y el 11 de octubre de 2019 fundó AGRS Co., Ltd., del cual es el director representante.","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TH","iso_639_1":"th","name":"ภาษาไทย","english_name":"Thai","data":{"biography":"","name":"โทโมกาซุ ซูงิตะ","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Томокадзу Сугита","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CZ","iso_639_1":"cs","name":"Český","english_name":"Czech","data":{"biography":"","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"IT","iso_639_1":"it","name":"Italiano","english_name":"Italian","data":{"biography":"Tomokazu Sugita è un doppiatore giapponese nato l'11 ottobre 1980 a Saitama, Giappone. Affiliato in precedenza ad Atomic Monkey, attualmente è il CEO di AGRS Co., Ltd. Il suo gruppo sanguigno è B.\n\nSugita e il collega Narita Ken vengono talvolta definiti “fratelli” a causa di una battuta fatta durante la Live Pastel Collection 2003. Durante un evento di “Omaera No Tame Darou”, i conduttori Toshiyuki Morikawa e Nobuyuki Hiyama hanno chiesto a Sugita in che modo si somigliassero. La sua risposta è stata che entrambi sbattono raramente le palpebre, rendendo il contatto visivo con l'uno o con l'altro un incontro spaventoso.\n\nSugita ha anche una stretta amicizia con il collega Yuichi Nakamura dal 2001. Entrambi interpretano i protagonisti maschili di due anime tratti dalle visual novel di Key, rispettivamente Yuichi Aizawa di Kanon e Tomoya Okazaki di Clannad.\n\nSugita ha vinto il premio \"Miglior attore di supporto\" al terzo Seiyu Awards.\n\nIl 1° aprile 2020 ha lasciato l'agenzia Atomic Monkey, a cui è stato legato per tanti anni, per dedicarsi al suo ruolo di direttore rappresentativo in AGRS Co., Ltd., intrapreso l'11 ottobre 2019.","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","iso_639_1":"pt","name":"Português","english_name":"Portuguese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Tomokazu Sugita","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"UA","iso_639_1":"uk","name":"Український","english_name":"Ukrainian","data":{"biography":"Суґіта Томокадзу (яп. 杉田 智和, нар. 11 жовтня 1980) — японський сейю. Переважно виконує ролі юних чоловіків, та відомий своїм «глибоким басовим голосом», часто виконує імпровізації та пародіювання.","name":"Томокадзу Суґіта","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"杉田智和是日本的男性聲優。埼玉縣出身。原屬 Atomic Monkey，2020 年 4 月 1 日現在是個人事務所 AGRS 代表。\n\n代表作有《涼宮春日的憂鬱》、《銀魂》等。","name":"杉田智和","primary":false}}]}},"tv_298849_credits":{"at":1773470201782,"data":{"cast":[],"crew":[],"id":298849}},"person_3212771_translations":{"at":1773491792090,"data":{"id":3212771,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"","name":"Yan Zixian","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"严子贤，1994年5月2日出生于四川省遂宁市，毕业于北京现代音乐研修学院，中国内地影视男演员。","name":"严子贤","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"RU","iso_639_1":"ru","name":"Pусский","english_name":"Russian","data":{"biography":"","name":"Янь Цзы Сянь","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"嚴子賢","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"엄자현","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"VN","iso_639_1":"vi","name":"Tiếng Việt","english_name":"Vietnamese","data":{"biography":"","name":"Nghiêm Tử Hiên","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"嚴子賢，1994 年 5 月 2 日出生於四川省遂寧市，畢業於北京現代音樂研修學院，中國內地影視男演員。","name":"嚴子賢","primary":false}}]}},"person_2887206_translations":{"at":1773578266065,"data":{"id":2887206,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"张雨濛是一名配音演员。2022年7月23日，配音的动画《神澜奇域无双珠》在爱奇艺播出。","name":"张雨濛","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Yumeng Zhang (张雨濛) is a Chinese voice actress.","name":"Yumeng Zhang","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"TW","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biogra